INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'dbba4ed2-4569-45e8-a19f-0844db62c883',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Foundry: Efficient Testing with Hardhat Tasks and Plugins$escape$,
  $escape$When writing smart contracts with Foundry, testing is crucial. Hardhat tasks and plugins simplify this process. To start, create a new task using `@foundry/hardhat-task` and define it in `tasks.ts`. For example, `const { task } = require('@foundry/hardhat-task'); task('test', 'Run tests').setAction(async (args, env) => { const ethers = await env.ethers; const contract = await ethers.getContractFactory('MyContract'); const instance = await contract.deploy(); await instance.deployed(); });`. Next, install required plugins, like `@nomicfoundation/hardhat-ethers` for ethers.js integration. Then, create a new Hardhat task to fork a local node using `@foundry/hardhat-task` and `@foundry/hardhat-fork-manager`. This allows for seamless testing with a local Ethereum node.$escape$,
  $escape$const { task } = require('@foundry/hardhat-task'); task('test', 'Run tests').setAction(async (args, env) => { const ethers = await env.ethers; const contract = await ethers.getContractFactory('MyContract'); const instance = await contract.deploy(); await instance.deployed(); });$escape$,
